# Docker build-context excludes for the root `Dockerfile` (image: credence-dagster).
#
# ⚠️ DELIBERATELY MINIMAL. The Dockerfile ends in `COPY . .` and the box job resolves
# SPORTS_DBT_DIR=/app/quant_sports_intel_models/sports_dbt out of that copy — so an over-broad
# ignore here silently removes code the box needs and the failure shows up only at runtime.
# Add a pattern only when you are sure nothing in the image reads it.
#
# NCAAF-P1.1: `sports_dbt` materializes its DuckDB into the project dir on a laptop run (the
# profile's default path is the project root). Those files are gitignored, so a CD build from a
# clean clone never sees them — but .dockerignore is a SEPARATE list, and a build from a working
# tree would COPY a multi-hundred-MB database into the image (311 MB observed 2026-07-20).
*.duckdb
*.duckdb.wal
